Skretting Aquaculture Research Centre A/S (Skretting ARC) was established in 1989, and is the central R&D unit for the global fish and shrimp feed concern Skretting, which is owned by Nutreco N.V. Nutreco’s head office is in Amersfoort, The Netherlands. Skretting ARC's main objective is to provide research and technical support regarding fish and shrimp feed. Skretting ARC has about 60 manyears of which about 45% have degrees corresponding to MSc or PhD level. It has an international staff representing 13 nationalities. It performs research for all feed companies within Skretting in Europe, North & South America, Asia and Australia. Skretting ARC’ is a legal entity owned 100% by Skretting AS.
